Utterances.UttText: CC: chest pain HPI: Gerry Cage is a 46yo M with HTN presenting with 4 months of occasional exertional chest pain.

Phrases.PhraseText: with 4 months of occasional exertional chest pain.

Utterances.UttText: He notes he has had 3 episodes prior of 1-2 seconds of sharp chest pain with exertion, but a few days ago he experienced 5-10 minutes of sharp chest pain that "knocked the wind out of me" when carrying groceries.

Phrases.PhraseText: prior of 1-2 seconds of sharp chest pain

Utterances.UttText: The pain self-resolved in 10 minutes with resting.
At that time he reports feeling lightheaded.
At that time, he denied n/v, sweating, diarrhea, cough, sob, or palpitations.
He also reports feeling substernal pressure after eating lunch several times a week.

Phrases.PhraseText: feeling substernal pressure after eating lunch several times

Utterances.UttText: The pressure is not associated with specific foods, but worse when he eats a lot.
He is concerned about the chest pain with his significant family history of cardiac disease.
